note.p:
The list of keywords that have become reserved includes (a) all binary operators spelled as NCNames
            (for example, and, div);
          (b) keywords that can appear at the start of a clause in a FLWOR expression, and that
          can be followed by a left curly brace (for example, for, let, where,
          while, return); and (c) a few other keywords (for example case and else)
          that can appear between two arbitrary expressions.
